comments.name: PR10IV
comments.text: L10I/V are polymorphic, PI-selected accessory mutations that increase the replication of viruses with other PI-resistance mutations.

comments.name: IN66CDEFGHLMNPQRSVWY_-
comments.text: T66A/I/K are non-polymorphic mutations selected primarily by EVG. T66K is associated with high-level EVG resistance, intermediate/high-level RAL resistance, and low-level DTG and CAB resistance. Its effect on BIC is not known. T66P is an unusual mutation at this position.

comments.name: IN263K
comments.text: R263K is selected in vitro by EVG, DTG, and BIC, and in patients receiving DTG. It reduces DTG and BIC susceptibility about 2-fold and EVG susceptibility somewhat more.

comments.name: IN163RK
comments.text: G163R/K are polymorphic in subtype F viruses from ARV-naive patients but are otherwise non-polymorphic. They are common INSTI-selected mutations. Alone, they have little, if any, effect on INSTI susceptibility.

comments.name: IN50I
comments.text: M50I is a polymorphic mutation selected in vitro by DTG and BIC in combination with R263K. It appears to contribute to reduced DTG susceptibility in combination with R263K.

comments.name: CABIntermediate
comments.text: This virus is predicted to have intermediate-level reduced susceptibility to CAB. The use of the combination of CAB/RPV should be considered to be contraindicated.

comments.name: DTGIntermediate
comments.text: There is evidence for intermediate DTG resistance. If DTG is used, it should be administered twice daily.
